A notorious armed robbery suspect has been arrested by the Special Anti-Robbery Squad of the Imo State Police Command. The Special Anti-Robbery Squad of the Imo State Police Command said it has arrested a suspected notorious armed robber, Kelvin Eze. According to reports, Eze, 33, was arrested in connection with a robbery incident in Owerri, the state capital. A police source disclosed that on February 25, 2018, at Emmanuel College, Owerri, one Kingsley Iheanacho was robbed at gunpoint and his Toyota Avalon car was taken away, adding that the stolen Avalon, coupled with other cars; a laptop; razor blade; and marijuana were recovered from the suspect. Source